    - target: {fileID: 5502387711208104083, guid: a01cfc34c5d09034dbd62d1a7d2cc505,
        type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_Text
      value: 'Computers are made up of various devices, each playing a specific role
        in the overall functioning of the system. These devices can be grouped into
        distinct categories based on their primary function: input devices, output
        devices, storage devices, and processing units.


        Input devices are
        the tools that allow users to send data and commands into the computer. Examples
        include keyboards, mice, microphones, scanners, and webcams.

        Output
        devices handle the presentation of processed data back to the user. Monitors,
        speakers, and printers are typical examples, each providing visual, auditory,
        or physical outputs respectively.


        Storage devices are responsible
        for saving data for both temporary and long-term use. Hard disk drives (HDDs),
        solid-state drives (SSDs), flash drives, and memory cards store everything
        from applications to personal files.


        Finally, processing units,
        such as the CPU, execute instructions, process data, and coordinate the entire
        system''s operations. These units are essential for the computer to function
        effectively.


        Understanding these categories helps users appreciate
        how the different components of a computer work together, forming a complete,
        functional system capable of complex tasks.


        And that''s the end
        of the whole lectures.

        I don''t know if you studied them all but
        you''re all set astroquizzer!


        Omo werey you didn''t read anything.

        And
        if you see carry over now you go dey feel somehow.

        tufia!'
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 5999933893511949893, guid: a01cfc34c5d09034dbd62d1a7d2cc505,
        type: 3}
      propertyPath: infoText
      value: 'Types of Computer Devices by Function

        Click "F'' To Study'
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 5999933893511949893, guid: a01cfc34c5d09034dbd62d1a7d2cc505,
        type: 3}
      propertyPath: id
      value: Types of Computer Devices by Function
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 5999933893511949893, guid: a01cfc34c5d09034dbd62d1a7d2cc505,
        type: 3}
      propertyPath: activateDistance
      value: 2.76
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 5999933893511949893, guid: a01cfc34c5d09034dbd62d1a7d2cc505,
        type: 3}
      propertyPath: Content
      value: 'Computers are made up of various devices, each playing a specific role
        in the overall functioning of the system. These devices can be grouped into
        distinct categories based on their primary function: input devices, output
        devices, storage devices, and processing units.


        Input devices are
        the tools that allow users to send data and commands into the computer. Examples
        include keyboards, mice, microphones, scanners, and webcams.

        Output
        devices handle the presentation of processed data back to the user. Monitors,
        speakers, and printers are typical examples, each providing visual, auditory,
        or physical outputs respectively.


        Storage devices are responsible
        for saving data for both temporary and long-term use. Hard disk drives (HDDs),
        solid-state drives (SSDs), flash drives, and memory cards store everything
        from applications to personal files.


        Finally, processing units,
        such as the CPU, execute instructions, process data, and coordinate the entire
        system''s operations. These units are essential for the computer to function
        effectively.


        Understanding these categories helps users appreciate
        how the different components of a computer work together, forming a complete,
        functional system capable of complex tasks.


        And that''s the end
        of the whole lectures.

        I don''t know if you studied them all but
        you''re all set astroquizzer!


        Omo werey you didn''t read anything.

        And
        if you see carry over now you go dey feel somehow.

        tufia!'
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
